ul.li: Shared Offset 0x08: This byte offset is architecturally overloaded. In Internal pages, it stores the right_child Page ID. In Leaf pages, it stores the next_leaf pointer to enable $O(N)$ sequential range scans.
Slotted Logic: cell_pointers grow downwards from 0x0C; IndexCell data grows upwards from the end of the 4096B buffer.

g.title: Used for data storage and range scans
